main event: Two airmen observed a self-luminous object the size of a full moon changing colors to orange at Keesler AFB.
interesting points: The object was observed for a duration of 5 to 15 minutes., The object was estimated to be about 60 feet in diameter and 1000 feet in altitude., The object traveled at an estimated speed of 600 to 700 mph and made abrupt turns., The sighting data was deemed insufficient for analysis., No photographs were included in the report.
